<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idee684406-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s957"><num value="957">§ 957.</num><heading> Definitions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">When used in this chapter—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idee684407-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s957/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> The term “person” includes individuals, partnerships, corporations, and associations;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idee684408-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s957/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> The term “Secretary” means the Secretary of Agriculture.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idee684409-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/act/1936-06-24/ch745/s7">June 24, 1936, ch. 745, § 7</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/49/1899">49 Stat. 1899</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
